The methods for investigating interlinkages among targets across the nine goals in the PRD involve two steps: cross-impact matrix assessment and network analysis. First, the cross-impact assessment explored mutual target influences using 7-score scale from Nilsson et al. (2016), ranging from +3 (most positive) to −3 (most negative) (Table 4
                           ). Positive scores indicated synergies, whereas negative scores indicated potential tradeoffs. Scores were assigned through expert surveys and literature review conducted by the co-authors. Experts were invited to score one target’s influence on another and provide insights based on their expertise. The co-authors also reviewed relevant documents to collect scoring evidence. The guiding question during this process is “how will actions to achieve this target will affect the achieving that target?”. Table 5
                            presents examples of scoring pairs of influencing and influenced targets.
